// Assume we have two processors, CPU0 and CPU1\n\n// Step 1: Disk I/O is initiated by CPU0\ndiskController.initiateRead();\n\n// Step 2: Disk controller signals an interrupt to the APIC when the read is complete\napic.signalInterrupt(diskInterrupt);\n\n// Step 3: APIC routes the interrupt to an appropriate CPU based on its configuration\n// For example, it might route it to CPU0 for locality\napic.routeInterrupt(diskInterrupt, CPU0);\n\n// Step 4: CPU0 handles the interrupt by executing the interrupt service routine (ISR)\nCPU0.executeInterruptServiceRoutine(diskInterrupt);